The incident reported in Kaunas does indeed highlight the importance of considering potential fire hazards, especially with the use of Li-ion batteries, which are known to be highly flammable when subjected to thermal stress. However, it serves as a cautionary tale rather than a definitive cause-and-effect situation.

As an experienced entrepreneur in energy solutions, I would strongly advise caution when selecting any energy generator, whether for home or business use. It is imperative to research thoroughly and ensure the manufacturer has a proven track record,